The Kirinyaga Council of Elders has asked Deputy Governor Julius Njiri to resign if he cannot work with Governor Joseph Ndathi(pictured).Bishop Cyrus Githaka said Ndathi s opponents are using Njiri to derail him. Addressing the press at a Kerugoya hotel, council officials said Njiri should respect the governor."Let Njiri come out clearly instead of fighting Ndathi, Githaka said.